Utterances: Hi, Im macie I'll be your nurse today. Can you Tell me your name and date of birth?
Hey! What's up?
Can you tell me your name and date of birth?
My name's Lucas Callahan and my birthday is . . . [Mr. Callahan reports correct birthday].
Can you tell me where you are?
I'm in the hospital. Where bodies come to heal and pudding comes to grow that little skin on top.
Can you tell why your here?
Those idiot cops brought me here. I don't need to be here but the front desk guy said that they have to check me out. Like I'm some sort of book in the history of atlases.
Can you tell me what caused the cops to bring you in?

Well, this cop stopped me when I was just taking care of my business. I had to check out some cars because I had a suspicion that there were government agents following me. It's probably good that I'm here, now. In any case, yeah. Cops are dumb. But I get it, I was running around kinda, and it's a grocery store parking lot, and 11:30 is a little late for track practice. Actually -- actually, it's always too late for track practice, but whatevah.
What kind of government agents were following you? (Clarified to Tell me more about the government agents?.)

I mean, what do you want to know? I just had a hunch they were in one of those cars, waiting to scoop me up and throw me in solitary. They know I'm enlightened and if my writings get out, boom, their secrets are overthrown. Not that I'm gonna let them stop me. (Clarified to to tell you more about the government agents.)
Ok (No matching questions found.)
Do you have any history of anxiety?

I'm not anxious or paranoid or whatever. I mean, I just have a really really fine-tuned sense of, like, OK, now they're coming for me, the government agents, and I have to be on the look out, 'cause no way am I being snatched up, not a chance.
Do you have any hallucinations?
No way. I don't see junk that's not there or anything.
Do you use any substances?
I do coke, I drink . . . that's really it. I like doing the same things over and over. I get in my groove with it.
How often do you do coke?
I dunno, 2 or 3? It's more of a weekend party thing, not a, I need it to get out of bed sort of thing. Besides, who likes beds?
How often do you drink?

Not often -- 2 or 3 times a week, I guess. It's more of a party vibe than anything. I drink more when I'm down, but I'm not down anymore! It's all loose goose these days. I'm not, like, waking up with the hair of the dog. That's like, no hair and no dogs for me, thank you.
When was the last time you used drugs?
Haven't done coke since about four days ago, I'd say.
How well do you sleep at night?
Well, there's not much of it, but I get a couple hours in usually, and I never feel, like, unrested or anything. Recently, I haven't had to sleep for like, four days. It's sick, completely bangin'.
How is your energy levels?
Awesome! I mean, I'm just a high energy kind of guy, a lot of the time. But this week especially I've felt, like, crazy up and up, and I love it. I just love it. I feel like I could lift a horse.
How do you feel right now?

I'm feeling great. Actually, I'm like, mega great. Ha, I just thought of, like, a 20-foot-tall cheese grater. Anyway, yeah, I'm not bad or anything, I was brought here by the cops. Who doesn't love a pleasant ride in a locked car with malevolent strangers?
Do you have any health conditions?
Not really. They diagnosed me with depression, but I'm really not worried about that anymore. I'm just really not in that headspace right now.
When did they diagnose you with depression?

We're dredging up this junk--well, I got diagnosed with depression like three years ago. Three little pigs. Wonder what happened to the third pig . . . I bet he got diagnosed, too. Squealer. It's like going fishing and pulling up an old boot.
Do you take any medications for depression? (Clarified to Do you take medication for depression?.)
I used to, yeah. (Clarified to if I take medication for depression.)
Do you currently? (No matching questions found.)
Do you currently take medications?

I've only ever been on antidepressants, and not anymore. That stuff dulls your vibes. Y'all should be careful about giving it out too much. You're gonna have a Shadowville full of zombies with no zookeeper. Meow.
Can you tell me about your typical moods?
You've got Option A and Option B. With A, we're talking about a bottomless rat hole. With B, we're talking good vibes that don't disappoint. I'll stick with B, thanks.
What do you mean when you say bottomless rat hole?
I mean, depression sucks? I don't know what you want me to say.
Do you have any frequent mood changes? (Clarified to Do you often experience mood changes?.)

I guess some have won. I've never felt better but--sure, there have been times when the big D-E-P cast its shadow over me. Left the Peachy King in a dark place. But then there's a depression recession and things get better. My mood can change a couple times a year, but who's marking the calendar? (Clarified to if I often experience mood changes.)
When was your last period of depression?

I mean . . . I fully got out of it maybe a couple months ago . . . it started a while before that. I dunno. Time isn't really linear, you know? I don't think in terms of, like, oh, this happened, now this'll happen.
Can you tell me your reason for seeing a psychiatrist? (Clarified to What was your reason for seeing a psychiatrist?.)

I mean, that doctor was a buffoon, but I get where he was coming from -- I had just tried to kill myself. That doesn't necessarily scream NOT depressed, you know? Like, your eyeballs are your eyeballs. You see what you see. (Clarified to what led me to see the psychiatrist.)
Can you tell me more about when you tried to kill yourself?
I don't know what you want me to say, it was -- I just don't wanna talk about it, OK? I just, I don't -- just focus on the present. This is all that's going on with me.
Do you currently have suicidal thoughts? (Clarified to Are you planning suicide?.)

Aw, come on, bud, do I seem like the type? I haven't even considered planning that sort of thing since maybe 3 years ago, and that's when I actually went through it. (Clarified to if I am planning suicide.)
Do you want to be dead?
No! Really, that's not me. That's not -- it gets like -- obviously, when you're depressed, you think like that, sure. But that's not me anymore, so whatever. I'm not worried about it.
Have you had any other suicide attempts?
Just the once . . . and you really don't have to worry about me like that.
What thoughts of suicide do you have?
It doesn't . . . I'm not really thinking like that right now, there's no way it's coming back. It's not even a problem.
Do you believe that others would be better off if you were dead? (Clarified to Do you ever feel that others would be better off if you were dead?.)
. . . No. Do I feel like that? No. That's all I care to say. No. (Clarified to if I feel that others would be better off if I were dead.)
Do you have any homicidal urges?
. . . Wow, what a lovely question. No, I don't. I can't believe you would even ask that.
Do you self harm yourself without intending to die?
No, not at all. Such a bummer question. I only really got like that during my one suicide attempt. One as in done.
I apologize for asking you these personal questions, I just want to make sure that you are okay.
Save your tears for the whales! I'm doing awesome.
Do any of your family members have any history of medical health issues?

Well, I don't know anything about my birth parents. But my actual parents are super healthy. They go for, like, jogs on the beach while talking about what sort of flaxseed goes best in kale smoothies. You can't take them anywhere.
Do you have any allergies?
Not at all. I'm allergic to bad vibes is all. That stuff is palpable. Like, oh boy, it's pollen season.
Do you have any home medications?
I'm not on anything these days. Stopped those antidepressants a while back. Zombie pills, honestly. Stuff is necrotic.
What side effects occurred when you took those pills? (Clarified to What kind of side effects have you experienced from medications?.)
Dude, just drop it, OK? It doesn't matter. Jeez Louise. (Clarified to what medication side effects I have experienced.)
I am just trying to gather important information so I can see what I can do to help you
Whatever. I literally could NOT be any better.
What prescription were you on? (Clarified to What were the details of the prescription you took?.)

All I remember is that they didn't work, they made me feel like . . . whatever, they sucked. They were--they were suck pills. That's all I remember. They were suck pills made in Sucksville and I hope they rot in Sucks Hell. (Clarified to what the details of my prescription were.)
What is your perception of mental health?

My brain is superb, honestly. It's frickin' cotton candy and sports car up there. Don't worry about me. Like, yeah, I was depressed before, if that's what you're asking. But that's as dead as a doornail, hangnail, all the nails.
Do you think that mental health is important to every day living? (No matching questions found.)
Do you think that mental health is important to every day activities? (No matching questions found.)
Do others notice mood or energy shifts? (Clarified to Do others notice when your mood and energy changes?.)
Who knows what other people notice? Personally, I notice everything, but you can't expect every chump on the street to be enlightened. (Clarified to if people notice when my mood and energy changes.)
Do you become excessively irritable or angry?
Sure, anger is a flower. I am a man of emotion. I feel everything, probably more than anybody else on earth. If a scamp interferes with my vibes, the anger blooms.
Do you have any racing thoughts/
Like a greyhound. Hyah! Hyah! But it works out great, because I'm working on this massive poem that's all about--well, it's gonna blow people's minds.
Do you have any changes in speed of moving or speaking?
I mean, nah, I'm just a super quick guy in general. I like to get things done and keep 'em moving. Talk fast, walk fast, all that. What can I say, some horses weren't meant for carriages.
Do you typically get in any fights or arguments?
My proverbial temper is lost on occasion. But all I do is argue! I'm not hurting anybody. My hands are clean.
Do you find pleasure and interest in typical activities?

Heck yeah, my life is the best. There's joy everywhere. There's joy in this hospital room, not that you would know much about that. Yeah, you really just gotta keep an eye out for it, my friend. Just squint and you'll see it.
Are you able to concentrate?

Oh, I've been laser-focused lately. On my poetry, that is. On my friends' projects. I told you we're thinking about making this community art center? It would be so sick. We'll see. It's all in the works.
Have you had any changes in productivity?
Yeah, definitely. Very astute question. I've been workin on this epic poem for the past--yeah, it's gonna annihilate poverty. Truth bombs non-stop. I've been working on it for the past week.
Have you had any changes in sexual activity and in libido?
My carnal business has definitely amped up in the past week! And I'm not complaining, either. It's been totally awesome. Friends and strangers, the sexy time has been unreal.
Do you wear protection during sexual intercourse? (No matching questions found.)
Do use protection during sexual intercourse? (Clarified to Do you have safe sex?.)
I can't remember the last time I did. I mean, this life is about pleasure, you know? Like, what are we if we're not having fun? (Clarified to if I have safe sex.)
Have you noticed any changes in social activity?
My social game has been through the roof in the last week. Not to be braggadocio, but I dosey doe with the best of them.
do you have any spending habits?
Well, I'm spending on the stuff that matters. I'm talking about a little cocaine here, some rare books there. I help my friends out however I can because you know? I'm a giver.
Have you had any consequences with these choices? (No matching questions found.)
Do you have any consequences with these choices? (No matching questions found.)
Are there any consequences? (Clarified to Are there consequences to how you spend money?.)

Philosophically speaking, there are consequences to everything. I publish my epic poem soon and the world surrenders to my word. I spend money and my parents get mad at me. That's just how it is. But I'm not dwelling on the bad stuff anymore. That's over, all gone. (Clarified to if there are consequences to how I spend money.)
Can you tell me about your self-concept?

I see myself as this visionary poet who's going to rock the world once his work is published. I see a killer head of hair that ladies just can't resist. I see an enlightened soul that shines like stained-glass. Amen, let the choir sing.
How is your financial status?
My finances are good! My parents give me some dough every now and then, I don't have to work . . . it's pretty stellar, ideal even!
Do you have any occupation?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
Do you currently have a job?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
Whats your occupation?
I'm in between jobs right now. Actually, I'm more in between not having a job and not having a job.
How are you handling not having a job? (Clarified to What is the reason you are currently unemployed?.)

I'm not trying to get a job right now and interrupt my vibes. I've got plenty going on with this poem I'm writing, which is going to be massive, by the way. It'll probably weigh fifty pounds by the time I print the thing out. Volumes, no joke. My parents probably wish I had a job, but whatever, they give me some money, so I'm chilling. (Clarified to why I am not employed.)
Do you have any legal troubles?
Not at all! I'm the patron saint of innocence! Hah. No, really though, I've never gotten so much as a ticket.
What is your method of transportation?
Oh, how do I get around? I'm cruising the streets in my car. I got it when I turned sixteen and that thing's like a brother to me.
Can you tell me about your diet?

I eat a little meal once a day and I'm game for whatever. I like a baguette with some cheese. I like carrots--there's nothing better than sharing carrots with a friend, the old pass-the-carrot. I like a roast chicken. Whatever, bring it on! Hot sauce never hurt, neither. Drip drop, baby don't stop.
How much fluids do you typically drink? (Clarified to How much fluid do you normally drink?.)

Uh, I don't keep track, I'm not a marine biologist. What am I, a marine biologist? Hah. Just, like, writing down how much water I drink. That's -- that's hilarious. Like some loser with too many water bottles. Anyway, I dunno. A glass here or there, probably once a day-ish. (Clarified to how much fluid I normally drink.)
How much caffeine do you drink?
Oh, that stuff's for squares and yuppies, man. I stay away.
What is you level of education?
I did a year in college a while back.
Do you have access to healthcare?
Yeah, I'm on my parents' insurance. It's such a crock, though, these insurance goons and the Super Pharm Outlet Malls of America . . .
What is your living situation?

It's pretty perfect, honestly. No rent, no bills, no dusting. I just crash in my car or at a friends' place or wherever, then I wake up and start my day. Boom. Did you know the kookaburra never sleeps in the same tree twice? I think most people would make better decisions if they mimicked ornithology.
Do you have a history of abuse?
Dang, are you serious?! No, not at all. Dang, what a wet blanket question. No, that's never happened to me. Dang. Screwin' up the vibes.
What are your general symptoms?
I don't really have any, like, health problems. I came here 'cause the police brought me here. I'm not like, oh, time for surgery, my heart is a foot.
Are you in any pain?
Not at all. I'm all endorphins, baby.

Not now and not ever. (Clarified to if I get headaches.)
Any ear aches?
No, I can hear mountain goats making their way up a rocky ridge across the country. They have very serious faces, but their hearts are soft in the dead of winter.
Do you wear contacts or glass?

No, no, no. I haven't had any problems with my vision. In fact, my vision has only gotten better and better. My ability to really see what's going on around me. I'm not trapped in some dark room somewhere, just praying for sleep, I'm engaged. I'm locked in.

My stomach, otherwise known as Callahan's Gastropub, has a big A in the front window. Looks good and feels great.
